<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/61601AVSDPSGQNGMDBLSJQKNCHSPHMMLK>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Rhinestone Rainbow Standard";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Join us for the Rhinestone Rainbow Standard!</h1><span><br/></span>Celebrate Pride with an unforgettable 19+ evening of drag, live music, comedy, burlesque, and dazzling variety entertainment – all in support of a great cause. This vibrant fundraiser brings together community, creativity, and self-expression while raising funds for charity.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Featuring talented performers from across the Fraser Valley and Lower Mainland, each artist generously donates their time and talent to help support the cause and create an evening of unforgettable entertainment. During pre-show and Intermission, you can browse a selection of handcrafted artisan goods from local vendors and makers, many of whom have also generously donated unique items for our charity raffle. Don't miss your chance to take home something special while supporting an important cause.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Whether you're part of the LGBTQ+ community or an ally, come enjoy a night of laughter, artistry, shopping, and rhinestone-studded Pride celebrations. Bring your friends, wear your sparkle, and get ready for a night where every rhinestone shines for a reason! The Rhinestone Rainbow Standard – where Pride, entertainment, community, and generosity come together for charity.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Performers</span><span><br/></span><ul><li>Addi Pose</li><li>Alter</li><li>Austin Tacious</li><li>Hailey Adler</li><li>Jamie Davis</li><li>Jay Kay</li><li>Lala Keisha</li><li>Maverick</li><li>Mimi Anmormi</li><li>Mina Mercury</li><li>Mkci</li><li>Ms Heart</li><li>Mya</li><li>ParaNorma PI</li><li>Phoenix & Jazzy</li><li>Sophia Diamonds</li><li>Venus ThighTrap</li><li>Zella Bones</li></ul><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>About the Charities We're Fundraising For</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">QMUNITY:</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>QMUNITY is a Vancouver-based non-profit organization serving as British Columbia's queer, trans, and Two-Spirit resource center. It focuses on improving 2SLGBTQIA+ lives through free counseling, peer support groups, educational workshops, and community-building resources.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Key aspects of QMUNITY include:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><ul><li>– Support Services: Offers low-cost, specialized counseling for 2SLGBTQIA+ individuals and gender-affirming chest wear.</li><li>– Community Space: Provides a safe, inclusive physical space for connection, as well as virtual services.</li><li>– Education & Training: Delivers \"Queer Competency Training\" to help organizations, businesses, and service providers create more inclusive environments.</li><li>– Advocacy & Resources: Hosts community events (e.g., Trans Day of Remembrance), provides resources for navigating discrimination, and helps find inclusive housing.</li></ul><span><br/></span>The organization operates on principles of anti-oppression, intersectionality, and reconciliation.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Friends For Life:</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Founded in 1993, and built on the belief that no one should have to face the many challenges of HIV/AIDS, cancer and other serious illness alone, the Vancouver Friends for Life Society is a holistic wellness centre with a comprehensive list of support services. Our mission is to provide emotional, informational, spiritual, and practical support to people living with life-challenging illness. Our philosophy recognizes the connection between mind, body, and soul with a view towards supporting the whole person rather than focus solely on the illness.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Our wellness programs are intended to complement primary medical care. Offered in a safe, and confidential environment, these programs are designed to help our members gain control over their health and to reduce anxiety, stress, and isolation from managing their illness.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Vancouver Friends for Life Society welcomes people in Vancouver and the Lower Mainland facing life challenges associated with HIV, hepatitis C, cancer and other life-interrupting illnesses to participate in specialized support programs.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Trans Lifeline:</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Trans Lifeline (translifeline.org) is a grassroots, non-profit organization offering direct emotional and financial peer support to trans and nonbinary people in crisis. Run entirely by trans people, it provides a safe, confidential hotline (US: 877-565-8860; Canada: 877-330-6366) that operates without involving police, fostering a \"by trans, for trans\" community support model.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Key aspects of Trans Lifeline include:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><ul><li>– Peer Support Hotline: A lifeline for trans individuals, including those questioning, to talk with fellow trans people.</li><li>– Abolitionist Approach: The hotline does not involve police or other involuntary emergency services unless explicitly requested by the caller.</li><li>– Support for Loved Ones: A dedicated Family & Friends Hotline is available for allies and support systems.</li><li>– Microgrants: Financial assistance programs designed to help trans individuals, particularly with legal name changes or other immediate needs.</li></ul><span><br/></span>The organization aims to improve the quality of life for trans individuals by providing connections, resources, and care.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>About The Rhinestone Phoenix Charity Foundation</h2><span><br/></span>The Rhinestone Phoenix Charity Foundation has been a part of the Vancouver LGBTQIA+ community since 1980, with our first Mr. and Ms. Gay Vancouver B.C. Richard McGuiness and Pussy Galore. The \"Gay\" titles were held under the advisement of the Dogwood Monarchist Society for the first four years.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Ms. Gay 4 Wiggins wanted to give her Mr. Gay Vancouver Crema a unique step-down gift; a society to call their own. The Founders played a crucial role in the establishing of the new society. The Founders included Emperor 8 Paul Landriault, Empress Emeritus Dame Rita Rhinestone, Ms. Wiggins and Miles Laphen. It was at this time that Crema's fantasy title was used in the creation of the society's name: The Phoenix Heraldic Society.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Over the years, many people have held the title of Mr. and Ms. Gay Vancouver, using this platform to move onto other organizations such as Two-Sprit United and The DMS in Vancouver and beyond. The Society has gone through many changes including a name change in 1997 to their current name The Rhinestone Phoenix Charity Foundation.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In their history, the organization has also awarded the Legacy title Miss Gay Vancouver and in 2009 they introduced the Mx Gay Vancouver title.<span><br/></span>
""";
